This article is a presidential memorandum issued by Barack Obama on March 6, 2012. The memorandum delegates certain responsibilities to the Secretary of State regarding the Treaty Between the Government of the United States of America and the Government of the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland Concerning Defense Trade Cooperation. The Secretary of State is delegated the function of making certifications, reports, and notifications to Congress prior to the treaty's entry into force and providing annual reports thereafter. Additionally, the Secretary of State is responsible for notifying Congress of amendments to the Implementing Arrangements made under the Defense Trade Cooperation Treaties Implementation Act of 2010. The memorandum concludes by authorizing the publication of the memorandum in the Federal Register.